# `ROTL`

**Visibility:** Private

### Signature

Cryptal describes a contract that the function implementation must comply with. SAW proves that the implementation matches this contract.

```cryptol
{n} (n < w) => [w] -> [w]
```

Type parameters are compile-time generic inputs (for example widths and lengths), not runtime function arguments.

| Component | Details |
|-----------|---------|
| Type Parameters | `n` |
| Constraints | n < w |
| Parameters | `x`: [w] |
| Returns | [w] |

Computes a sequence of w bits from `x`.

### Related Properties
- [rotationEquivalenceRelationsHold — Rotation Equivalence Relations Hold](../properties/misc.md#rotationequivalencerelationshold--rotation-equivalence-relations-hold)

### Cryptol Definition

```cryptol
ROTL x = x <<< `n
```
